# Vim-mode counterpart to mouse_editor_cursor.test. A left-click in
# the editor body places the cursor on that line AND must NOT
# inadvertently change mode (NORMAL stays NORMAL — only the chip
# click on the statusline mode-segment toggles input style).
command editor.use_vim
write doc.txt "ED01\nED02\nED03\nED04\nED05\nED06\nED07\nED08\nED09\nED10\nED11\nED12\nED13\nED14\nED15\nED16\nED17\nED18\nED19\nED20"
open doc.txt
command view.toggle_tree
expect screen contains "NORMAL"
expect screen contains "Ln 1"

# Same coords as the standard-mode test: y=10 ⇒ file line 9.
click 40 10
expect screen contains "Ln 9"
expect screen contains "NORMAL"
